bug.short_desc: Environment checks "os.name" and "os.version" fail for Windows Phone 8.1

long_desc.thetext:
Attached you find a screenshot of the navigator-Object inside a WebView. For IE use our feature detector.
In the end, both WebView and Browser should return correct environment checks.
Keep in mind to fix that for next as well.

I added the Windows Phone to the "detection list" and also added a basic unit test in next#master with b5fb3bd7b2d6847dffd63934a7de8c8fa9c041b7 qooxdoo#master with 9a4d329e18cdf69c5638d88e020b117ae2eaa068 qooxdoo#branch_4_1_x with 35b23ed9645268443166775e7eba1899f4cb3a30

I reviewed the fix and also took a look at other relevant environment-keys on our both Windows Phone (the blue HTC with WinPhone 8.0 and the Nokia Lumia 830 with WinPhone 8.1). There are still some issues because Microsoft now uses a confusing overblown UserAgent containing "Android", "iPhone" and whatever... :(
bad results in our featureconfigurator app:
1. IE on WP8.1: - "browser.name": is "mobile chrome" but should be "iemobile" - "browser.version: is "4.0" but should be "11.0" - "os.version": is "4.0" but should be "8.1"
2. IE on WP8.0 and WebView on WP8.1: - "os.version": is "" but should be "8.1"

I checked this key against Windows phone user agent: "device.name", "browser.name", "browser.version", "os.version", "os.name", "engine.name", "engine.version"
Fixed in next#master with 4726eea41d68fc44da92407d4c4dd3c08aa65fb0 qooxdoo#master with ac6d7d3691d104bb261af6c3eb2ddf3e10c99142 qooxdoo#branch_4_1_x with 35fa8910c29d4ecf621129b9409cb99c766e6c16
